title: Garden Pavilion and Latticed Gallery with an Alternative Design plate 365 from the publication "L'Art de Treillageur ou menuiserie des jardins"
description: Elevation of a domed garden pavilion with an arcaded gallery on either side.  The elevation is split in half and each section shows an alternative design.  The greatest difference is presented in the cupola.  Inscription across the top margin.  Indication of the scale at the lower margin.  Small inscriptions throughout.
name: Print
